properties.name: LineageRelationshipType
properties.description: Used by LineageAssertion to describe the nature of the line of descent of a work product component from a prior Resource, such as DIRECT, INDIRECT, REFERENCE.  It is not for proximity (number of nodes away), it is not to cover all the relationships in a full ontology or graph, and it is not to describe the type of activity that created the asserting WPC.  LineageAssertion does not encompass a full provenance, process history, or activity model.

objecttypes.name: DepositionGeometryType
objecttypes.description: The Deposition Geometry classification (corresponding to Energistics RESQML DepositionMode). Examples are parallel to top, parallel to bottom, etc.

objecttypes.name: LineageAssertion
objecttypes.description: Defines relationships with other objects (any kind of Resource) upon which this work product component depends.  The assertion is directed only from the asserting WPC to ancestor objects, not children.  It should not be used to refer to files or artefacts within the WPC -- the association within the WPC is sufficient and Artefacts are actually children of the main WPC file. They should be recorded in the data.Artefacts[] array.

models.name: OSDU-Metamodel_TDM
models.description: Type Definition Model for the OSDU Metamodel

objects.name: AbstractGeologicUnitInterpretation
objects.description: Common properties for entities describing an opinion of a volume-based geologic feature or unit.

objects.name: AbstractInterpretation
objects.description: The group of properties shared by different kinds of interpretations

objects.name: AbstractWPCGroupType
objects.description: Generic reference object containing the universal group-type properties of a Work Product Component for inclusion in data type specific Work Product Component objects

objects.name: AbstractWorkProductComponent
objects.description: Generic reference object containing the universal properties of a Work Product Component for inclusion in data type specific Work Product Component objects

objects.name: Artefacts
objects.description: An array of Artefacts - each artefact has a Role, Resource tuple. An artefact is distinct from the file, in the sense certain valuable information is generated during loading process (Artefact generation process). Examples include retrieving location data, performing an OCR which may result in the generation of artefacts which need to be preserved distinctly

objects.name: AuthorIDs
objects.description: Array of Authors' names of the work product component.  Could be a person or company entity.

objects.name: BusinessActivities
objects.description: Array of business processes/workflows that the work product component has been through (ex. well planning, exploration).

objects.name: CreationDateTime
objects.description: Date that a resource (work  product component here) is formed outside of OSDU before loading (e.g. publication date).

objects.name: DepositionGeometryType
objects.description: The Deposition Geometry classification (corresponding to Energistics RESQML DepositionMode). Examples are parallel to top, parallel to bottom, etc.

objects.name: Description
objects.description: Description.  Summary of the work product component.  Not the same as Remark which captures thoughts of creator about the wpc.

objects.name: FeatureName
objects.description: Name of the feature the Interpretation refers to

objects.name: GeoContexts
objects.description: List of geographic entities which provide context to the WPC.  This may include multiple types or multiple values of the same type.

objects.name: HorizonInterpretation
objects.description: Geologic information associated to horizon-related object types (marker, seismic picks, modeled objects etc)

objects.name: IsDiscoverable
objects.description: A flag that indicates if the work product component is searchable, which means covered in the search index.

objects.name: IsExtendedLoad
objects.description: A flag that indicates if the work product component is undergoing an extended load.  It reflects the fact that the work product component is in an early stage and may be updated before finalization.

objects.name: IsIntrusive
objects.description: Corresponding to Energistics GeologicUnitMaterialEmplacement 'intrusive' and 'non-intrusive'.

The assertion is directed only from the asserting WPC to ancestor objects, not children.  It should not be used to refer to files or artefacts within the WPC -- the association within the WPC is sufficient and Artefacts are actually children of the main WPC file. They should be recorded in the data.Artefacts[] array.

objects.name: MaximumThickness
objects.description: The maximum thickness of the StratigraphicUnitInterpretation.

objects.name: MinimumThickness
objects.description: The minimum thickness of the StratigraphicUnitInterpretation.

objects.name: Name
objects.description: Name

objects.name: OSDUSystemProperties
objects.description: System properties to be injected at root level by the OsduSchemaComposer script.

objects.name: OlderPossibleAge
objects.description: Represents the older possible age for the interpretation. Expressed in geological time as millions of years [Ma], and the value must be positive. The age value is not subject to normalization.

objects.name: ResourceKind
objects.description: The kind or schema ID of the artefact. Resolvable with the Schema Service.

objects.name: SequenceStratigraphicSchemaType
objects.description: Valid if Stratigraphic role type is set to Chronostratigraphic ex.: GeneticSequence

objects.name: SpatialArea
objects.description: A polygon boundary that reflects the locale of the content of the work product component (location of the subject matter).

objects.name: SpatialPoint
objects.description: A centroid point that reflects the locale of the content of the work product component (location of the subject matter).

objects.name: StratigraphicColumn
objects.description: Representation describing the vertical location of rock units in a particular area

objects.name: StratigraphicColumnRankInterpretation
objects.description: A global hierarchy containing an ordered list of stratigraphic unit interpretations

objects.name: StratigraphicColumnRankInterpretationSet
objects.description: Array of StratigraphicColumnRankInterpretation[] the StratigraphicColumn is composed of

objects.name: StratigraphicColumnRankUnitType
objects.description: Type of all stratigraphic units in this rank, i.e. Erathem

objects.name: StratigraphicColumnValidityAreaType
objects.description: Geographical area where a local stratigraphic column is valid: Basin, Region, Field, Segment

objects.name: StratigraphicRoleType
objects.description: The role or type of stratigraphy, e.g., Chronostratigraphic, Lithostratigraphic, etc.

objects.name: StratigraphicRoleType
objects.description: Geological concept used to produce the type, i.e. lithostratigraphy

objects.name: StratigraphicUnitInterpretation
objects.description: One of potentially many boundary interpretations as a single consistent description of a local boundary feature. An interpretation is subjective and very strongly tied to the intellectual activity of the project team members.

objects.name: StratigraphicUnitInterpretationSet
objects.description: Array of Stratigraphic Unit Interpretations the StratigraphicColumnRank is composed of. Units are ordered by ascending age or apparent depth.

objects.name: SubmitterName
objects.description: Name of the person that first submitted the work product component to OSDU.

objects.name: Tags
objects.description: Array of key words to identify the work product, especially to help in search.

objects.name: ValidationDate
objects.description: Date of validation of a custom stratigraphic column, start of validity

objects.name: ValueChainStatusType
objects.description: Member where the custom stratigraphic column has been produced: Exploration, FieldDevelopment, Production, LateLife

objects.name: YoungerPossibleAge
objects.description: Represents the younger possible age for the interpretation. Expressed in geological time as millions of years [Ma], and the value must be positive. The age value is not subject to normalization.

objects.name: acl
objects.description: The access control tags associated with this entity.

objects.name: ancestry
objects.description: The links to data, which constitute the inputs.

objects.name: createTime
objects.description: Timestamp of the time at which initial version of this OSDU resource object was created. Set by the System. The value is a combined date-time string in ISO-8601 given in UTC.

objects.name: createUser
objects.description: The user reference, which created the first version of this resource object. Set by the System.

objects.name: has
objects.description: The object reference identifying the DIRECT, INDIRECT, REFERENCE dependency.

objects.name: hasColumnStratigraphicHorizonBase
objects.description: Base Stratigraphic Horizon bounding the stratigraphic unit  in a context of a stratigraphic column (Denormalized information) and not in an context of a model which can have several interpretations. Expecting one single horizon.

objects.name: hasColumnStratigraphicHorizonTop
objects.description: Top Stratigraphic Horizon bounding the stratigraphic unit in a context of a reference stratigraphic column (Denormalized information) and not in an context of a model which can have several interpretations. Expecting one single horizon.

objects.name: hasDepositionGeometryType
objects.description: The reference to the deposition geometry type (Energistics RESQML DepositionMode) of this StratigraphicUnitInterpretation. RESQML BUSINESS RULE: The deposition mode for a geological unit MUST be consistent with the boundary relations of a genetic boundary. If it is not, then the boundary relation declaration is retained.

objects.name: hasDomainType
objects.description: Describes the domain of the interpretation: Depth, Time, Mixed

objects.name: hasFeature
objects.description: Reference to the Feature the Interpretation refers to. The actual type of the target is specified in the specialisation, i.e. the type, which includes this schema fragment.

objects.name: hasFeature
objects.description: The reference to a local rock volume feature, to which this interpretation is associated.

objects.name: hasGeologicUnitShapeType
objects.description: The relationship to a GeologicUnitShapeType like sheet, dyke, dome, mushroom, channel and more.

objects.name: hasLithologyType
objects.description: The relationship to a LithologyType, corresponding to Energistics GeologicUnitComposition.

objects.name: hasResource
objects.description: The SRN which identifies this OSDU Artefact resource.

objects.name: hasRole
objects.description: The SRN of this artefact's role.

objects.name: hasSequenceStratigraphySurfaceType
objects.description: Describes the horizon sequence stratigraphic information (flooding, ravinement, maximum flooding, transgressive)

objects.name: hasStratigraphicRoleType
objects.description: Describes the horizon stratigraphic role (chronostratigraphic, lithostratigraphic, biostratigraphic)

objects.name: hasStratigraphicRoleType
objects.description: The reference to the stratigraphic role type (Energistics RESQML StratigraphicUnitKind) for this StratigraphicUnitInterpretation.

objects.name: id
objects.description: Previously called ResourceID or SRN which identifies this OSDU resource object without version.

objects.name: isConformableAbove
objects.description: Defines whether the stratigraphic unit above the horizon is conformable

objects.name: isConformableBelow
objects.description: Defines whether the stratigraphic unit below the horizon is conformable

objects.name: kind
objects.description: The schema identification for the OSDU resource object following the pattern {Namespace}:{Source}:{Type}:{VersionMajor}.{VersionMinor}.{VersionPatch}. The versioning scheme follows the semantic versioning, https://semver.org/.

objects.name: legal
objects.description: The entity's legal tags and compliance status. The actual contents associated with the legal tags is managed by the Compliance Service.

objects.name: meta
objects.description: The Frame of Reference meta data section linking the named properties to self-contained definitions.

objects.name: modifyTime
objects.description: Timestamp of the time at which this version of the OSDU resource object was created. Set by the System. The value is a combined date-time string in ISO-8601 given in UTC.

objects.name: modifyUser
objects.description: The user reference, which created this version of this resource object. Set by the System.

objects.name: tags
objects.description: A generic dictionary of string keys mapping to string value. Only strings are permitted as keys and values.

objects.name: version
objects.description: The version number of this OSDU resource; set by the framework.

focusObject.name: OSDUSystemProperties
focusObject.description: System properties to be injected at root level by the OsduSchemaComposer script.
